data.title: Here’s What Manhattan looked like in the 1960s
data.meta_description: The 1960s in Manhattan was a melting pot of ideas, with Greenwich Village at its heart. Here, you'd find smoky coffeehouses filled with beatnik poets, fervent debates, and the strumming of acoustic guitars.
